<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I zoned into HoH to check out the new mob.
<br />

<br />
Valorian Guardian Kreike was up, cons yellow to 70.
<br />

<br />
There were two mobs next to him, but they were just normal for the area, so I figured I'd give it a shot and see what he can do.
<br />

<br />
Charmed up a standard guardian from the right wing and parked him in the tunnel corner.  Went over and pacified the two next to the named.  Pulled with tash just to see what it would do and ran back to where my pet was.  Named came single and for kicks I tried to root it.  Same as the sentries... no go on the root.
<br />

<br />
Sent in the pet next and the pet got instant agro.  Which I find odd as he never would do that before when I pulled with a tash.
<br />

<br />
Wham Bam Splat
<br />

<br />
Pet goes from 100% to 75% in the 5ish seconds it takes for me to slow.  Which "mostly" landed the first try.
<br />

<br />
Pet was SoSalik and NDT'd only.  By the time the mob had pet to 10%, my pet had him to 93%.  This took less than 40 seconds.  Pet was hitting for usual 300-500 shots.
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately, I don't run with all damage showing (I hate the spam) so I don't know what he was crushing my pet for.
<br />

<br />
He was totally melee and didn't seem to proc or AoE anything detrimental.  Just massive HP and insane damage.
<br />

<br />
Well, just thought I'd share the info I found.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
